header.gameNote: COACHES VS CANCER CLASSIC AT SYRACUSE NY

article.headline: Princeton 61, Bucknell 48
article.story: SYRACUSE, N.Y. (AP) -- Luke Owings scored 21 points to lead Princeton to a 61-48 victory over Bucknell on Thursday night in the opening round of the Coaches vs. Cancer Classic. The Tigers (1-0) will play No. 6 Syracuse in the second round on Friday night. The host Orange (1-0) beat Northern Colorado 104-54 on Thursday night. Owings had 16 points in the first half, including three 3-pointers. John Griffin had 18 points for the Bison (0-1), who shot only 30.4 percent for the game. "It was a good opening game for us," Princeton's first-year head coach Joe Scott said. "I really liked our defensive effort." Kevin Bettencourt, the Patriot League's leading scorer last season, had 10 points for the Bison. Bucknell overcame a nine-point deficit in the first half to take an 18-16 lead with 4:27 to play. The Bison also cut an eight-point deficit to three 8½ minutes into the second half. "We would get into those stretches offensively that we kick ourselves in the butt," Bucknell head coach Pat Flannery said. "We try and make the perfect play. We dribble drive when we should have just kicked out for an easy bucket." Princeton guard Scott Greenman's length-of-the-court layup after a steal gave the Tigers a 53-41 lead with 5:37 to play.
